source_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-27T04:10:00Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\"generation\":1,\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"openai/gpt-5.5-fast\"},\"resolveArtifactRootUsed\":false}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":1,\"iteration\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Current interface packet inventory and post-009 landed state\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First pass established the actual on-disk interface packet, alias mismatch, and which 009 expansion recommendations already landed.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What is the current interface skill surface?\",\"Which prior expansion recommendations already landed?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What is the current interface skill surface?\",\"Which prior expansion recommendations already landed?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Treat .opencode/skills/sk-design/interface as the physical packet path\",\"reason\":\"The hub registry resolves workflowMode interface to packet design-interface; no interface directory exists on disk.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json:16\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:14\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/mode-registry.json:16\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/research.md:55\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/assets/interface_preflight_card.md:16\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:18:00Z\",\"durationMs\":480000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"iteration\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Routing benchmark bottlenecks and score discrepancy\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.72,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Added benchmark-specific evidence: current report shows 70/100 conditional, not the stale 78/100 prompt value, with two concrete intra-router failures.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which routing failures most constrain usefulness?\",\"Does the benchmark confirm the operator-provided 78/100 score?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Which routing failures most constrain usefulness?\",\"Does the benchmark confirm the operator-provided 78/100 score?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Optimize for a generic aggregate score without scenario diagnosis\",\"reason\":\"The benchmark names routed-intra as the headline bottleneck and identifies ID-011 and ID-005 as first-failing scenarios.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:35\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:5\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:17\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:19\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:50\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:55\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:26:00Z\",\"durationMs\":480000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Efficiency improvements in router resource loading\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.55,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Converted benchmark D3 and resource-map evidence into precise router changes: split overloaded grounding and encode route-away outcomes.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"How can the interface skill reduce reads while preserving quality?\",\"Which router branches should split or become route-away outputs?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"How can the interface skill reduce reads while preserving quality?\",\"Which router branches should split or become route-away outputs?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Remove references broadly to improve D3 efficiency\",\"reason\":\"D2 discovery is high and D5 connectivity is perfect; the defect is overload/precision in specific branches, not a lack of connectivity.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:18\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:111\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:117\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:119\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.json:421\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.json:360\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:34:00Z\",\"durationMs\":480000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":4,\"iteration\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Usefulness, UX, and handoff gaps\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.34,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Added remaining user-facing gaps: redesign intake, handoff manifest, reference lookup status line, and visual asset strategy boundaries.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What would make the interface skill more useful to operators?\",\"What UX/handoff gaps remain after the reference expansion?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What would make the interface skill more useful to operators?\",\"What UX/handoff gaps remain after the reference expansion?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Turn Mobbin/Refero into a required lookup for every design task\",\"reason\":\"The design reference doc makes paid live references optional and non-blocking; required lookup would block ordinary work and violate the fallback rule.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md:40\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-process/real_ui_loop.md:90\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/design-grounding/design_references_mcp.md:75\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/taste-skill.md:783\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/taste-skill.md:804\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/taste-skill.md:262\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:42:00Z\",\"durationMs\":480000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":5,\"iteration\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Manual testing, benchmark coverage, and verification gaps\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.18,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Mostly confirmed existing hypotheses and added verification-specific actions around non-recursive playbook validation and unscored live dimensions.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"How should improvements be verified?\",\"Which manual testing gaps should become automated or benchmark-backed?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"How should improvements be verified?\",\"Which manual testing gaps should become automated or benchmark-backed?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Claim improvement from doc edits without rerunning benchmark and playbook checks\",\"reason\":\"The current benchmark leaves D1-inter and D4 unscored, and the playbook states per-feature completeness needs a structural sweep until validation recurses.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:23\"}],\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:130\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:144\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:501\",\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md:64\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:50:00Z\",\"durationMs\":480000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":6,\"iteration\":6,\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Prioritized improvement synthesis and explicit do-not list\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.04,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Final pass found no materially new source classes; it consolidated priorities, dependencies, and eliminated alternatives.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"What are the prioritized improvements and do-not list?\",\"Has the loop converged?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"What are the prioritized improvements and do-not list?\",\"Has the loop converged?\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Add more aesthetic preset files as the main improvement\",\"reason\":\"The current aesthetic cue index already warns cues are critique-against only, not a chooser; additional presets risk weakening the anti-default contract.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/aesthetics/README.md:26\"},{\"approach\":\"Bulk-import the external corpus into interface references\",\"reason\":\"The prior 009 synthesis rejected bulk import; leverage is operational gates and cards, not volume.\",\"evidence\":\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/research.md:158\"}],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.1867,\"madScore\":0.2965,\"entropyCoverage\":1,\"compositeStop\":0.65},\"sources\":[\"file:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/research.md:68\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/references/aesthetics/README.md:28\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:187\",\"file:.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md:253\"],\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:56:00Z\",\"durationMs\":360000,\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\"generation\":1,\"totalIterations\":6,\"answeredCount\":10,\"totalQuestions\":10,\"stopReason\":\"converged\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-27T04:58:00Z\"}\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/001-interface/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-strategy.md\n+# Deep Research Strategy - Interface Skill Improvement\n+\n+## 1. OVERVIEW\n+\n+### Purpose\n+\n+Investigate practical improvements to the `sk-design` interface mode, grounded in the live `design-interface` packet, prior 009 reference/asset research, the external 43-entry design corpus, manual testing playbook, and the routing benchmark.\n+\n+---\n+\n+## 2. TOPIC\n+\n+Improve the interface skill for efficiency, usefulness, UX, tooling, references, assets, and routing without weakening its anti-default design judgment.\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n+## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n+- [x] What is the current interface skill surface and physical packet path?\n+- [x] Which prior expansion recommendations already landed, and which remain useful?\n+- [x] Which routing benchmark failures most constrain efficiency and usefulness?\n+- [x] Which UX/handoff gaps remain after reference expansion?\n+- [x] Which validation gaps should gate follow-up implementation?\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n+\n+---\n+\n+## 4. NON-GOALS\n+- Do not implement skill changes in this lineage.\n+- Do not modify any path outside the fan-out artifact directory.\n+- Do not add aesthetic presets or bulk-import external corpus material.\n+- Do not claim benchmark improvement without rerunning the benchmark in a follow-up implementation packet.\n+\n+---\n+\n+## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n+- Stop when all key questions have evidence-backed answers and the final iteration adds low novelty.\n+- Stop no later than 10 iterations.\n+- Stop immediately if required evidence would require mutating outside the lineage artifact directory.\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n+## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n+- Current packet path is `.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/`; the prompt's `.opencode/skills/sk-design/interface` is a mode alias, not a physical directory.\n+- The 009 high-value interface expansions mostly landed: shared register, brief-to-dials, mechanical/content gates, preflight card, real-UI loop, design-system/reference grounding, and MCP tool docs.\n+- Current benchmark report is `CONDITIONAL` at 70/100, not the prompt's stale 78/100; bottleneck is `routed-intra`, specifically ID-011 and ID-005.\n+- Highest leverage improvements are routing precision, split resource maps, explicit route-away output, redesign intake, required handoff manifest, and verification upgrades.\n+- Do-not list centers on avoiding preset expansion, paid-reference mandates, corpus bulk import, and implementation inside the research packet.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n+<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n+## 7. WHAT WORKED\n+- Current-state inventory first: prevented proposing references that already exist after 009. (iteration 1)\n+- Scenario-level benchmark reading: turned aggregate score into concrete ID-011 and ID-005 fixes. (iteration 2)\n+- D3/resource-overload analysis: identified split-grounding as a surgical efficiency fix. (iteration 3)\n+- External corpus cross-check: preserved useful redesign and visual-asset ideas without bulk import. (iteration 4)\n+- Manual playbook review: exposed verification gaps and live-mode requirements. (iteration 5)\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n+## 8. WHAT FAILED\n+- Treating the prompt's `interface` path literally failed; the repo uses `design-interface` as the physical packet.\n+- Treating the prompt's 78/100 benchmark value as current failed; live report evidence says 70/100 conditional.\n+- Looking for a top-level spec document in the provided spec folder failed; the folder currently contains only `research/`, and write scope forbids seeding docs outside the lineage artifact directory.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n+## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n+\n+### Bulk reference expansion -- BLOCKED (iteration 6, 2 attempts)\n+- What was tried: Compare 009 matrix and current packet inventory.\n+- Why blocked: Most high-value interface references/assets already landed; adding more bulk would reduce efficiency and risk preset behavior.\n+- Do NOT retry: Do not propose wholesale external corpus import or more aesthetic-preset files as the lead improvement.\n+\n+### Prompt benchmark value as truth -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempt)\n+- What was tried: Search and read benchmark report artifacts.\n+- Why blocked: Current report says 70/100, conditional.\n+- Do NOT retry: Do not cite 78/100 unless a newer report artifact proves it.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n+## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n+- Treat `.opencode/skills/sk-design/interface` as a physical path: ruled out by `mode-registry.json` and filesystem evidence. (iteration 1)\n+- Optimize aggregate benchmark score without scenario diagnosis: ruled out because report names routed-intra and two failing scenarios. (iteration 2)\n+- Remove references broadly to improve D3: ruled out because discovery/connectivity are strong; overload is localized. (iteration 3)\n+- Require Mobbin/Refero for every design task: ruled out because lookup is optional, paid, and non-blocking. (iteration 4)\n+- Claim improvement from docs without benchmark/playbook verification: ruled out by unscored D1-inter/D4 and playbook validator limits. (iteration 5)\n+- Add more aesthetic preset files or bulk-import external corpus: ruled out by anti-chooser guardrails and 009 negative knowledge. (iteration 6)\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n+## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n+- Should redesign intake be a new small `references/design-process/redesign_intake.md` or folded into `real_ui_loop.md`? Recommendation: new small reference only if router can load it narrowly on redesign terms.\n+- Should benchmark fixtures be updated to expect `brief_to_dials.md` for ID-011, or should `MECHANICAL_PREFLIGHT` load it directly? Recommendation: do both only if a rerun confirms recall improves without unacceptable D3 cost.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n+## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n+Converged. Follow-up implementation should start with router fixes for ID-005 and ID-011, then rerun the design-interface benchmark and playbook structural checks.\n+<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n+\n+---\n+\n+<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n+## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n+- `resource-map.md` was not present in the provided spec folder; skipping spec-level coverage gate.\n+- The provided spec folder currently has only `research/`; this lineage did not create or mutate `spec.md` because the operator constrained writes to the lineage artifact directory.\n+- The routing benchmark report exists at `014-routing-benchmark/design-interface/skill-benchmark-report.md` and currently reports aggregate 70/100, conditional.\n+- Prior 009 research is high-signal but partly superseded by landed interface references/assets.\n+\n+---\n+\n+## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n+- Max iterations: 10\n+- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n+- Completed iterations: 6\n+- Stop reason: converged\n+- Artifact root override was bound directly; `resolveArtifactRoot` was not run.\n+- Writes were limited to `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/001-interface/research/lineages/gpt55fast`.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/015-per-skill-improvement-research/001-interface/research/lineages/gpt55fast/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+{\n+  \"sessionId\": \"fanout-gpt55fast-1782532104406-wgsfs7\",\n+  \"loopType\": \"research\",\n+  \"status\": \"complete\",\n+  \"openQuestions\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"oq-redesign-placement\",\n+      \"question\": \"Should redesign intake be standalone or folded into real_ui_loop.md?\",\n+      \"recommendedResolution\": \"Standalone only if the router loads it narrowly for redesign prompts; otherwise fold into real_ui_loop.md to avoid D3 overload.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"oq-preflight-benchmark-expectation\",\n+      \"question\": \"Should benchmark fixtures expect brief_to_dials.md for ID-011?\",\n+      \"recommendedResolution\": \"Add brief_to_dials.md to MECHANICAL_PREFLIGHT and rerun benchmark; keep only if ID-011 improves without excessive D3 regression.\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"rq-path\",\n+      \"question\": \"What is the current interface skill path?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"The hub mode is interface, but the physical packet is .opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"rq-benchmark\",\n+      \"question\": \"What benchmark score should research ground in?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"The curre